      <td width='100%' valign='top' class='post2'>
        <!-- THE POST 6487 -->
        <div class='postcolor'>                    RP = Raid Points<br>TRP = Total Raid Points<br>CRP = Current Raid Points<br><br>The amount of RP credited for a raid per member will be the sum of all RP spent divided by the number of members attending the raid, plus any bonus that the officers decide to give.<br><br>When we raid you should join the loot channel. This channel will be moderated until bidding is open. That means you will be unable to type anything in this channel, until the auctioneer opens the channel.<br><br>When a loot mob is killed, the slain will be resurrected and 5 min will be given if any one is LD. If you have just came back from LD it is your responsibility to enter cvloot as soon as you can, so you don't miss the auction.<br><br>Two messages will be given in the raid channel, one will be what is about to be auctioned the other will be a last call. The rest will all be done in the loot channel. It is your responsibility to make sure your channels are working. If they are not working you should inform the loot officer. There will be no waiting for members that are AFK.<br><br>All items drop will be put up at full RP Value to be bid in the loot channel. Once the auctioneer opens the channel for bidding you can use the following commands.<br><br>/bid		(Add you and your CRP to the roll)<br>/withdraw 	(Removes you and your CRP from the roll)<br><br>The auctioneer will give a 10 seconds pause from the last bid, at that time he will give a last call in the raid and loot channel. If no more bids are place with in 5 seconds after the last call, the auctioneer will close the bidding and the channel. The auctioneer will then post the spread in the loot channel and do random roll, based on the sum of all the bidders CRP and announce the winning in the raid.<br><br><ul>Priority is given to bidders in this order:<br><li>Has enough CRP for the item.<br><li>Have positive CRP but not enough for the item.<br><li>Has negative CRP.<ul><br><br>All priorities are allowed to bid but will be knocked out of the roll by a member with higher priority.<br><br>If no one bids on the item for the weighed roll, the item will then become a rot item <br><br>Rot items will be open to all mains and alts alike and start off at 1RP. Rot items will be auctioned in an open auction in the cvloot channel.<br><br>Once the item is determined to be a rot item. The auctioneer will inform cvloot that the item has become rot and will open the channel for open bidding. The auctioneer will give a 5-sec pause from the last bid until he starts closing the auction by doing a once, twice and sold statement. There has to be two or more members actively bidding on said item for the item to be awarded in this manner.<br><br>Alts will only be allowed to bid if they are in the zone and the item is NO DROP.<br><br>If less then two people bid in the open auction, the item will be awarded to a guest and no RP will be added to the raid worth for this item. If no guest(s) are attending the raid, an officer that can not use the item will loot and destroy it.<br><br><ul>The rules for rot loot:<br><li>No conversing on what you plan to bid.<br><li>No bargaining with other members to let you win.<br><li>No flaming of any one that bids.<br><li>Bidding over your CRP.<br><li>Rallying the members to let said item rot.<ul><br><br>Breaking any of these rules will result with a 10 attended raid suspension of bidding or receiving RP.<br>Rallying members to get an item to rot will result in said item being true rot and no one will loot except for guest.<br><br>Alts and 2+boxing will be allowed but only your main will be credited RP for any raid. If you are requested to bring your alt or 2+box by an officer, your alt will be reworded by having a mains loot rights for said raid. All RP will be credited and debited from the main's RP pool.                     <!--IBF.ATTACHMENT_6487--></div>
        
